main event: On April 9, 1960, three blinking lights were observed by a civilian in Cincinnati, Ohio.
interesting points: The observer noted that the objects were only blinking lights and did not resemble any known aircraft,The observation lasted approximately 2 minutes,The observer was a Roman Catholic priest pursuing a master's degree in psychology,The report did not provide sufficient details to reach a firm conclusion,The document included multiple questionnaires about the sighting without adequate data.
witness description: Civilian, a Roman Catholic priest, aged 33
